---
const faqs = [
	{
		question: "How does Fortify Security protect my data?",
		answer:
			"Fortify Security employs a multi-layered security approach, combining real-time monitoring, AI-powered threat detection, automated incident response, and enterprise-grade encryption. Our system continuously scans for vulnerabilities, identifies suspicious activities, and takes immediate action to contain any threats before they can compromise your data.",
	},
	{
		question: "Is Fortify compliant with industry regulations?",
		answer:
			"Yes, Fortify Security is fully compliant with major industry regulations including GDPR, HIPAA, SOC 2, ISO 27001, and PCI DSS. Our platform is regularly audited by third-party security experts to ensure we maintain the highest levels of compliance and data protection standards.",
	},
	{
		question: "How quickly can Fortify respond to security threats?",
		answer:
			"Our automated response system detects and responds to threats in an average of 125 seconds. When a security incident is identified, our platform immediately implements containment protocols, minimizes potential damage, and alerts your security team with detailed information about the threat and actions taken.",
	},
	{
		question:
			"Can Fortify integrate with our existing security infrastructure?",
		answer:
			"Absolutely. Fortify Security is designed to seamlessly integrate with your existing security tools and infrastructure. We offer robust API access, custom integrations, and support for industry-standard security protocols to ensure our platform enhances rather than replaces your current security investments.",
	},
	{
		question: "What kind of support does Fortify provide?",
		answer:
			"Fortify offers tiered support options based on your subscription plan. All customers receive email support and access to our comprehensive knowledge base. Professional and Enterprise plans include priority support, 24/7 phone support, and dedicated account managers who can provide personalized assistance and regular security reviews.",
	},
	{
		question: "How does Fortify handle data encryption?",
		answer:
			"Fortify implements military-grade encryption protocols to protect your data both in transit and at rest. We use AES-256 encryption, secure key management, and regular encryption rotation to ensure your sensitive information remains protected against unauthorized access at all times.",
	},
];
---
<div class="py-32 bg-white" id="faq">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4">
    <div class="text-center mb-20">
      <div class="inline-block px-6 py-2 bg-primary-100 text-primary-600 rounded-full mb-4">
        FAQ
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-6 bg-clip-text text-transparent bg-gradient-to-r from-primary-500 to-secondary-500">
        Frequently Asked Questions
      </h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Everything you need to know about our security solutions. 
        Can't find the answer you're looking for? Contact our support team.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <div class="space-y-6">
        {faqs.map((faq, index) => (
          <div class="collapse collapse-plus bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg hover:shadow-xl transition-all duration-300">
            <input type="radio" name="faq-accordion" checked={index === 0} /> 
            <div class="collapse-title text-xl font-medium p-6">
              {faq.question}
            </div>
            <div class="collapse-content px-6 pb-6 pt-0">
              <p class="text-gray-600">{faq.answer}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 text-center">
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">Still have questions? We're here to help.</p>
        <button class="btn btn-lg bg-primary-500 hover:bg-primary-600 text-white border-0 rounded-full px-8 shadow-lg hover:shadow-primary-200/50 hover:scale-105 transition-all duration-300">
          Contact Support
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 ml-2" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10.293 3.293a1 1 0 011.414 0l6 6a1 1 0 010 1.414l-6 6a1 1 0 01-1.414-1.414L14.586 11H3a1 1 0 110-2h11.586l-4.293-4.293a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
        </button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>